data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc` with `nint` and `nuint` into a `Span`.**

```csharp
Span<nint>  nints  = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

Both compile and run correctly. On this 64-bit system each element is 8 bytes. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` / `sizeof(nuint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't fixed at compile time), but the `stackalloc` itself works in safe code when assigned directly to a `Span<T>`.
